enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve modifying the bag's contents based on a collection, making them suitable for setting up similar test conditions.
The add method can be used to populate the bag with elements before testing retainAll, ensuring a consistent state.
The containsAll method can be used to verify that only the elements in the given collection are retained after retainAll is called.
The getCount method can be used to verify that the number of each retained element matches the expected count after retainAll is called.
